Frontend:
- Feature: Move the pages from the top of the page to a left side bar. This way, the pages are more visible and easier to access. The sidebar can also be collapsible to save space when not in use. If collapsed, a hamburger menu icon can be used to expand the sidebar when needed. This will improve the overall user experience and make navigation more intuitive. The sidebar doesn't scroll with the page, so it's always accessible, and it can also include icons for each page to make it more visually appealing. The icons should always be visible, even when the sidebar is collapsed, to provide quick access to the pages. Additionally, the sidebar can be designed to be responsive, adjusting its layout and visibility based on the screen size of the device being used. This will ensure that the navigation remains user-friendly across different devices, such as desktops, tablets, and smartphones.
- Feature: The top bar should be resevered for a back button (for navigation), the title of the page and maybe some quick actions, such as a search bar or a user profile menu. This will help to declutter the top bar and make it more focused on the content of the page. The title of the page should be prominently displayed at the left of the top bar near the back button, while quick actions can be placed on the right side for easy access. This will create a cleaner and more organized layout, improving the overall user experience.
- Feature: Add a bank account detail page where you have an overview of all the linked bank accounts. You can click on each account to see more details, such as transaction history, account balance, and options to manage the account (e.g., edit, delete, or add new accounts). Maybe it's best to combine the detail and the edit page.
- Feature: color positive amounts green and negative amounts red.
- Bug: There is a padding around the bank account table on the bank account collection page.

